Validations:

    - by default angular framework supports form validations.

    - "$error" is the predefined object used to store the form related errors.


Ex. Text Validation
-------------------

<form name="myForm">
    <input type="text"
           name="uname"
           ng-model="uname"
           ng-minlength="3"
           ng-maxlength="6"
           required>
     <p ng-if="myForm.uname.$error.minlength">*** Minimum 3 Characters are Required**** </p>
     <p ng-if="myForm.uname.$error.maxlength">****Maximum 6 Characters are Allowed***</p>
     <p ng-if="myForm.uname.$error.required">****Can't Left Blank****</p>
</form>



Validations by using ngMessages Module:
---------------------------------------

    - by using this module we can overcome data redundancy.
    - by using this module we can reuse the validation messages.


Steps to develop  the  validations by using ngMessages Module:
--------------------------------------------------------------

Step 1:
    download the ngMessages Module by using Gulp.

Step 2:
    Add the ngMessages Dependency.

Step 3:
    Create the Validation Messages with "ng-message" directive in separate file (messages.html).

step 4:
    import the validations from external file by using "ng-messages-include" & "ng-messages" directive





